My boyfriend got the Yimchurri tacos (sp?) which had carne asada, onion, cabbage, and salsa. Also very good (I made him give me a bite, I did not give him a bite of my food). The bar tender was delightful, knowledgeable of the menu, and quick to refill water and beer. Food came out in a reasonable amount of time, and the ambiance was nice: pretty chill with a pretty low level of noise the night we were there so we were able to chat at a normal volume. My husband and I are regulars at this bar coming almost every Saturday to see the boxing matches that they play. The last time we came service was very slow we didn’t complain but we didn’t tip either. So we went go to see the fight last night between Wilder and Fury. I’m pregnant but still attend to support my husbands love of boxing. I order tater tarts ($7.99) and a sprite ($2.99) with the only woman who is supposed to be servicing tables (On Saturdays she’s usually on first floor which is up the first set of steps at the small bar by the kitchen. She wears a long blonde wig and has a disturbing attire on because she wears clothes that are way too small). At first the woman ignores my request for help, I was feeling nauseous and needed a sprite to help my stomach a little. My husband has to find her to get her attention and ask her again for a sprite (which still didn’t come until about twenty minutes later but we were unfazed because we were watching the boxing match at this point). The woman tells my husband she needs his credit card for that to create a tab which has never happened to us at this bar, but without question he gives her his platinum American Express card that she takes and never returns with. My husband is so into the boxing match he doesn’t notice she never gave his card back but I did so I alerted him. He goes to find his card and finds the woman that took it, he asked if she can close his tab. She says okay and told him to go back to his table, she will bring his card. Well she didn’t. Instead she began taking shots with her friends, then she brought another soda we never requested but we thought it was a refill (you get three free refills) so we didn’t say anything. Meanwhile I remind my husband she has not returned his card. He goes two more times to try to get his card back finally being successful the third time because he literally stood there and waited for his card. She gives him his card and a receipt for $15 which doesn’t add up to what we bought. So my husbands in a respectful tone ask her why the receipt was so over priced. The woman says she charged for two sodas instead of giving a refill. My husband mentions the free refills we got the last time she served us. The woman’s exact words were “well you didn’t tip me last time either”. My husbands says okay mam forget about it and returns to the table watch the fight. This woman then proceeds to grab a security guard and brings him to our table. She says directly in front of us with the security guard to get him out of here now. Security tells my husband he has to leave and steps directly in front of him. Now my husband and I are both in school for law so we know when something happens with workers go straight to management. My husband request the manager who listens to the situation, checks our receipt (the tater tots and two sodas were still on the table as well), apologizes for the inconvenience, demands for security to leave our table, and says he will get on his worker about the matter. He said we shouldn’t have any more problems for the remainder of our stay, which we didn’t but the server no longer offered any service to us and continued to drink with her friends only serving the people around us. He also said he hopes this situation doesn’t disturb our relationship with the bar. Now this bar is a great go to spot for watching sports. The crowd is amazing and full of energy, the other employees are very respectful (and have been tipped), and the food is okay (even though I think it’s a little pricey and can take some time to cook). They shouldn’t have a waiter who is drinking on the job blatantly, begging for tips, and threatening to get people kicked out because they don’t tip her or she thinks she might not get a tip. This is an upscale bar, and really should not be delivering services with an employee of this manner. Every other employee on the job is usually very professional great workers, and always seek to make their customers happy.

I had a great time here tonight on the rooftop because it accommodated both my smoker friends and non smoker friends. This place didn't have a coat room which was a little annoying because holding my coat on the second floor dance room was not great because it was very crowded. I wore it for a little while on the second floor but it got too hot. The rooftop was excellent. There were a lot of heating lamps. There was great music and it was nice to be able to be with all my friends without half of the group going to smoke and the other half staying inside. The drink prices were expensive. Bud Light was $6 and a shot was $10. Not great if your trying to have a cheap night. The rooftop is in a different rating category because I would give it 4 stars and I would give the second floor 2.5 stars. The reason I didn't love the second floor was because of the over crowding and the sticky floors, it was hard to move.  Overall, it was fun and the staff was fast at getting drinks. The bouncer was cool, he loved my puma jacket. The guys managing the stairs were not very nice, but they have a job to keep people moving so it's understandable. Music was house, mainstream and typical club music. Good place for a night out.
